category: ALBERT CAMUS
category comment: 

clue: On Dec. 10, 1957 Albert Camus received this prize in Stockholm, Sweden

response: the Nobel Prize (for Literature)

clue: Dr. Bernard Rieux fights a rising epidemic (which symbolizes the Nazi occupation of France) in this Camus novel

response: La Peste (The Plague)

clue: Camus was born in this then French colony, the setting of some of his works

response: Algeria

clue: In the original French, the first line of this Camus novel is "Aujourd'hui, maman est morte"

response: The Stranger

clue: Camus' attack on Stalinism in 1951's "L'Homme revolte" strained his relationship with this other existentialist

response: Jean-Paul Sartre

